node.text:
Clover Club
.

The Clover Club cocktail can be traced back to the late 1800s and Philadelphia’s Bellevue-Stratford hotel. This popular hangout drew crowds of writers, lawyers and titans of industry, who convened to talk about issues of the day. Naturally, their meetings included drinks, and the Clover Club with gin, fresh lemon juice, raspberry syrup and egg white was a favorite among this genteel set.
.

.

Name: SMOKED DATES⁠
.⁠
Ingredients:⁠
•⁠
* 40ml  Bourbon⁠
* 40ml Graham’s Port 10 Years Old⁠
* 15ml Dates Syrup⁠
* Dash Angostura Bitter⁠
* Dash Lime Juice⁠
•⁠
Stir all the ingredients over ice, then strain into a Spey Whisky Glass @urbanbaruk over 1 large ice block. Add smoke for instant infuse with a smoking gun. This cocktail was smoked with Bourbon Soaked Oak Wood Chips. Garnish with Physalis berry & dry dates.⁠
